signal_description:
Calculate the percentage of duplicate event names in the defaultview-545 table. 
First, for each row in defaultview-545, count the total number of event_name values. 
Then, count the number of distinct (unique) event_name values. 
Subtract the number of distinct values from the total count to get the number of duplicates for that row.
Sum up the number of duplicates across all rows.
Divide that sum by the total count of all event_name values across all rows. 
Multiply by 100 to convert to a percentage.
